Ah, yes, I refactored the `InstanceIdDb.next()` implementation so it threw the `std::runtime_error` instead of returning `-EAGAIN`. This new behaviour aligns it with the existing behaviour in the code. However, the check you highlighted should be replaced with

```
try {
    rc = pldmInstanceIdDb.next(eid);
} catch (const& std::runtime_error e) {
    throw sdbusplus::xyz::openbmc_project::Common::Error::TooManyResources();
}
```

Shall we add one more catch to catch std::system_category().default_error_condition exception?
try {
    rc = pldmInstanceIdDb.next(eid);
} catch (const& std::runtime_error e) {
    throw sdbusplus::xyz::openbmc_project::Common::Error::TooManyResources();
} catch (int error)
